    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Feature already in Vim?\n\nNo\n\n### Feature description\n\nAn option like `:set confirm` that will _always_ confirm that you want to exit Neovim, regardless of whether you have unsaved buffers or not. I've tried implementing something like this as a plugin but it doesn't really work. ",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "To add some more context: the reason I want something like this is the following:\r\n\r\nI work in a huge Rust monorepo. In such a huge project, `rust-analyzer` takes like 1-2 full minutes to initialize. For that reason, I don't want to kill Neovim to get back to the terminal, instead I want to leave Neovim open and either use a terminal buffer or a new tmux window or use `:sus` to get to my shell, so that I don't have to close and re-open Neovim, then wait 1-2 minutes for `rust-analyzer` to re-initialize.\r\n\r\nDoes that make sense? I'm open to alternative solutions, but this seems like a simple solution to me.",
