        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> An option like `:set confirm` that will _always_ confirm that you want to exit Neovim, regardless of whether you have unsaved buffers or not.\r\n\r\nJust use `:qa!`.\r\n\r\nAs for your usecase about having to quit vim to get to the terminal, you can either start a terminal in neovim (`:term`), you can suspend neovim temporarily (`C-Z`), or you can use an external terminal multiplexer like `tmux`.\r\n\r\nEdit: Sry I misunderstood your issue.",
